7
00:00:59,032 --> 00:01:02,835
Item of business is commendations for Eagle Scout,

8
00:01:03,366 --> 00:01:04,527
for Mr. Andrew Knight.

9
00:01:08,690 --> 00:01:19,999
And at this time, I invite, I invite Counselor Marks up, whose motion this was to commend our friend, Andrew.

10
00:01:24,222 --> 00:01:25,163
Thank you, Mr. President.

11
00:01:28,461 --> 00:01:45,092
It's my honor and pleasure, Mr. President, tonight to recognize a young gentleman in our community who has put in countless hours to rise to the top of being a Boy Scout.

12
00:01:45,872 --> 00:01:53,998
And anyone that's been in the Scouts realizes that you go through different levels to attain the highest level, which is Eagle Scout.

13
00:01:54,798 --> 00:01:57,180
And it's many countless hours of

14
00:01:57,910 --> 00:02:06,459
community participation, it's many countless hours of obtaining badges, field trips, and then leadership within the scouts.

15
00:02:07,260 --> 00:02:11,004
And here we have a young gentleman in pack 416.

16
00:02:13,546 --> 00:02:19,769
And that's the Otis Street Church, United Methodist Church, that sponsors the PAC.

17
00:02:20,449 --> 00:02:30,174
And over the last, let's say, three or four years, I've had the privilege of recognizing many Eagle Scout recipients.

18
00:02:31,134 --> 00:02:33,855
from the Otis Street Pack.

19
00:02:34,575 --> 00:02:43,777
And they've done yeoman's work in representing our community and putting out young gentlemen of Andrew's caliber within our community.

20
00:02:44,818 --> 00:02:46,218
Just a few things I'd like to state.

21
00:02:46,938 --> 00:02:53,080
Andrew earned 28 merit badges, 21 of which were Eagle required.

22
00:02:54,260 --> 00:03:01,827
He had various positions in the troop, including patrol leader, assistant senior patrol leader, and senior patrol leader.

23
00:03:03,108 --> 00:03:11,475
As part of the Eagle Scout, every Eagle Scout is required to submit a community service project.

24
00:03:12,336 --> 00:03:15,338
And we've had a number of Eagle Scouts within our community.

25
00:03:16,079 --> 00:03:22,164
The last one I recall was an Eagle Scout that fixed the flagpole when it came down during a hurricane,

26
00:03:22,520 --> 00:03:23,940
in front of the Medford Public Library.

27
00:03:24,541 --> 00:03:27,081
And he did a fundraiser and raised funds and so forth.

28
00:03:27,842 --> 00:03:31,703
And he also put some shrubbery and bushes around that and erected our flag.

29
00:03:32,243 --> 00:03:37,444
And Andrew came up with a great concept as part of his project.

30
00:03:38,225 --> 00:03:42,246
I'd like for him to say a few words on the project itself.

31
00:03:43,626 --> 00:03:46,527
And you know, most of the times I ask,

32
00:03:47,253 --> 00:03:49,055
people, would you like to come up and say a word or two?

33
00:03:49,795 --> 00:03:52,858
And Andrew, without hesitation, said, absolutely.

34
00:03:53,618 --> 00:03:55,440
So he must be a gifted speaker.

35
00:03:55,460 --> 00:03:57,261
Uh-oh.

36
00:03:57,902 --> 00:03:59,223
I set the table for you now.

37
00:04:00,564 --> 00:04:02,646
So Andrew would like to say a few words.

38
00:04:03,286 --> 00:04:10,592
One other point I'd like to mention is when you look at Eagle Scout, it's not just the scout that's going through it.

39
00:04:11,013 --> 00:04:13,555
It's the mom and dad, which we have in the audience tonight.

40
00:04:14,055 --> 00:04:24,689
that, as they could probably attest to, spend many countless hours on these projects and chaperoning the scout around and so forth, and they participate as well.

41
00:04:24,749 --> 00:04:28,233
But an interesting fact is only about 5% of all Boy Scouts

42
00:04:29,735 --> 00:04:32,397
attain the rank of Eagle Scout.

43
00:04:33,137 --> 00:04:43,083
And since 1912, when this was established, there has been 1,700,000 Boy Scouts that have earned the rank of Eagle Scout.

44
00:04:48,967 --> 00:04:59,270
That may sound like a lot, but we're talking over 100 years worth of millions of Boy Scouts, hundreds of millions of Boy Scouts throughout this country.

45
00:04:59,970 --> 00:05:04,211
And it's really, truly a big honor to obtain this level.

46
00:05:04,611 --> 00:05:08,852
So at this point, I'd like to pass it over to Andrew so he can explain his community service project.

47
00:05:11,070 --> 00:05:13,031
I'd like to thank you for inviting me here.

48
00:05:13,451 --> 00:05:23,056
And for my community service project, I decided to do it for the Medford Boys and Girls Club located on Forest Street, because I've been going there as a kid ever since I was six years old.

49
00:05:23,096 --> 00:05:27,838
I've been going school years and summers, and it's kind of like a place that I've grown up at.

50
00:05:27,898 --> 00:05:33,341
So when it was time for me to do a project for a community, it was easy for me to decide to do something for them.

51
00:05:33,981 --> 00:05:37,623
So I went to the club director, Lisa Gosbecki, and I talked to her about

52
00:05:38,175 --> 00:05:41,777
the type of things that you would need at the Boys and Girls Club that would benefit them the most.

53
00:05:42,397 --> 00:05:54,404
And she told me that some type of recycling-oriented thing would help the kids learn about recycling and help them dispose of recycling materials properly, because at the time, they only had trash.

54
00:05:55,044 --> 00:06:05,210
So I then went back and made a plan to build a recycling center that would sort the recycling machine, paper, plastic, and cans, and then designed a recycling program that

55
00:06:05,567 --> 00:06:14,550
had games and activities that would teach the kids about recycling so that they could learn and take the knowledge home about what you're supposed to do with these materials so that it can better our environment.

56
00:06:15,230 --> 00:06:23,553
So then with my troop, I coordinated the building of the recycling center and then designed games and made activities for the kids.

57
00:06:23,713 --> 00:06:26,174
And I presented it at a family night at the Boys and Girls Club.

58
00:06:26,194 --> 00:06:28,395
So there were families there, kids there.

59
00:06:29,115 --> 00:06:34,317
And I was able to present the box and the information to everyone there so that

60
00:06:34,808 --> 00:06:36,168
they could learn about recycling.

61
00:06:36,288 --> 00:06:40,490
And it also worked as my Eagle Scout project after all the time I put in.

62
00:06:40,530 --> 00:06:42,870
And that was basically the impact it had on the community.

63
00:06:42,930 --> 00:06:44,411
A lot of the kids learned about recycling.

64
00:06:44,451 --> 00:06:54,934
They learned things that they've never heard about before, like how long it takes for things to decompose, because you never really think about that when you might throw away a styrofoam cup in the trash.

65
00:06:54,994 --> 00:06:57,755
But in reality, that thing never decomposes.

66
00:06:57,795 --> 00:07:02,616
So they're more aware of what they're doing now, and they can better the environment.

67
00:07:16,431 --> 00:07:18,733
So as we can see, Andrew will be in good company.

68
00:07:20,053 --> 00:07:34,183
Eagle Scouts, Neil Armstrong, Michael Bloomberg, Method Man, Stephen Breyer, Judge Breyer, President Gerald Ford, Donald Rumsfeld, Secretary of State, Steven Spielberg.

69
00:07:34,723 --> 00:07:37,585
So you're in a real elite group, Andrew.

70
00:07:38,225 --> 00:07:42,488
And at this time, I'd just like to present the Method City Council accommodation.

71
00:07:42,986 --> 00:07:53,049
says the Memphis City Council takes pleasure in awarding this council accommodation to Andrew Knight, Eagle Scout, Court of Honor Troop 416, on attaining this high ranking within scouting.

72
00:07:53,589 --> 00:08:00,151
The realization of this outstanding achievement will undoubtedly lead to success and accomplishments throughout your life.

73
00:08:00,651 --> 00:08:04,952
Signed by Council President Frederick De La Russo and myself, City Council, Michael Marks.

74
00:08:04,972 --> 00:08:06,913
Thank you very much.

75
00:08:13,064 --> 00:08:15,344
If we could take a picture out here, that'd be great.

76
00:09:06,349 --> 00:09:06,883
Can you hear the smoke?

77
00:09:35,399 --> 00:09:36,486
Congratulations.

78
00:10:02,275 --> 00:10:05,317
Chair recognizes Councilor Caviello for motion to suspension of the rules.

79
00:10:05,718 --> 00:10:06,659
Thank you, Mr. President.

80
00:10:06,679 --> 00:10:11,743
Mr. President, if we could take up motion number 16679, Mr. President.

81
00:10:12,443 --> 00:10:17,848
On the motion of Councilor Caviello to take out of order, paper number 16679.

82
00:10:18,308 --> 00:10:19,189
All those in favor?

83
00:10:19,869 --> 00:10:20,510
Aye.

84
00:10:20,870 --> 00:10:21,771
All those opposed?

85
00:10:22,711 --> 00:10:25,814
The ayes have it.

86
00:10:25,834 --> 00:10:27,515
16-679 offered by Councilor Caviello.

87
00:10:27,535 --> 00:10:30,758
Be it resolved that Medford City Council request the mayor

88
00:10:31,227 --> 00:10:37,951
to install a traffic light at the corner of High Street and Alston Street at the Brooks School for the Safety of Children.

89
00:10:38,552 --> 00:10:42,274
Many parents have contacted me since the side of school about this problem.

90
00:10:42,835 --> 00:10:43,495
Mr. Counselor.

91
00:10:44,055 --> 00:10:44,896
Thank you, Mr. President.

92
00:10:44,936 --> 00:10:48,859
Mr. President, fortunately, we come here tonight.

93
00:10:48,899 --> 00:10:56,964
Though I had this on the agenda last week, we come here tonight because a young man was struck last Friday night by a car.

94
00:10:57,344 --> 00:11:00,046
Fortunately, he was not injured.

95
00:11:00,671 --> 00:11:01,592
He was slightly injured.

96
00:11:02,072 --> 00:11:03,514
His parents are here tonight.

97
00:11:03,574 --> 00:11:07,797
And I say, thank God he wasn't hurt seriously, which is a saving grace.

98
00:11:08,218 --> 00:11:14,663
But Mr. President, that's been a problem on that corner for many years since my children went to school there.

99
00:11:15,544 --> 00:11:22,030
And in this day, with the traffic increasing and more people distracted driving,

100
00:11:23,252 --> 00:11:25,073
The road is becoming heavier and heavier and heavier.

101
00:11:26,614 --> 00:11:29,536
People don't adhere to the crosswalks.

102
00:11:29,616 --> 00:11:34,679
Even though there's a crossing guard there during the day, there's a lot of school activities there in the evening.

103
00:11:35,419 --> 00:11:41,182
And the Brooks School is one of the heaviest for after school programs in the city.

104
00:11:41,763 --> 00:11:46,325
So I think at this point, some changes need to be made on that corner.

105
00:11:47,326 --> 00:11:49,207
And in my opinion, I would think

106
00:11:49,786 --> 00:11:54,154
A street light should be installed with maybe a flashing light.

107
00:11:54,975 --> 00:11:55,155
St.

108
00:11:55,195 --> 00:11:57,800
Raphael's has a light in front of theirs.

109
00:11:58,721 --> 00:11:58,902
St.

110
00:11:58,942 --> 00:12:00,604
Joseph has a light in front of their school.

111
00:12:04,207 --> 00:12:08,430
There's some easy things we could do to make that area better also.

112
00:12:08,590 --> 00:12:12,173
One is, in the evening, getting rid of those orange lights.

113
00:12:12,653 --> 00:12:21,060
They're dim and they don't, I mean, for the few pennies that we're saving on them, it's not worth it to have them there.

114
00:12:21,080 --> 00:12:29,526
I think we need to put either LEDs or go back to the bright white lights so people can see it both in front of the school and on the side.

115
00:12:29,926 --> 00:12:34,407
where all the kids come out at 5 o'clock when the parents go by to pick them up on Auburn Street.

116
00:12:34,847 --> 00:12:35,988
Again, that's a dark area.

117
00:12:36,968 --> 00:12:47,171
And maybe, you know, one of the parents gave me some suggestions here about changing some markings that a highway person gave them.

118
00:12:47,751 --> 00:12:53,052
And some simple things like putting the markers in the middle of the road during the day.

119
00:12:53,752 --> 00:12:55,953
Because people are coming through that way now because

120
00:12:56,861 --> 00:12:59,562
Route 16 is a nightmare to get down to from route two.

121
00:13:00,082 --> 00:13:02,783
So now everybody's coming down route 60 to get the 93.

122
00:13:03,244 --> 00:13:05,705
So the cars are getting, you know, they're just traffic.

123
00:13:05,745 --> 00:13:06,545
It's just increasing.

124
00:13:06,965 --> 00:13:11,627
Speed is increasing and people they're on the cell phones and they're texting and they're not paying attention.

125
00:13:11,667 --> 00:13:12,087
Mr. President.

126
00:13:12,467 --> 00:13:19,150
So at this point I would, I would ask that we ask the mayor to immediately requisition the traffic light to be put there.

127
00:13:20,631 --> 00:13:20,931
Thank you.

128
00:13:20,971 --> 00:13:24,152
Counselor chair recognizes vice president Longo Kern.

129
00:13:24,445 --> 00:13:25,605
Thank you, President De La Russo.

130
00:13:25,645 --> 00:13:28,726
I just want to thank Councilor Caviello for putting this on the agenda.

131
00:13:28,906 --> 00:13:37,007
I knew it was going to come up because all of us have got the phone calls and emails with regards to the complaints and what happened Friday night, and it's pretty disturbing.

132
00:13:37,187 --> 00:13:39,788
And thank God the child is okay.

133
00:13:44,889 --> 00:13:48,209
I agree wholeheartedly there should be a traffic light.

134
00:13:48,389 --> 00:13:51,690
And I also think part of this is, you know, the enforcement

135
00:13:52,782 --> 00:14:02,504
quite possibly putting a, somewhere on the road, putting a speed limit sign so people know how fast they're going, because I think speeding has a factor.

136
00:14:02,944 --> 00:14:08,485
And when we don't have enough enforcement, it obviously leads to the speeding.

137
00:14:08,566 --> 00:14:17,828
So I've brought that up many, many times, to have speed limit signs like we have on Elm Street put in different locations in the city, especially near the schools.

138
00:14:17,908 --> 00:14:19,648
So I would just like to add that.

139
00:14:20,101 --> 00:14:24,584
somewhere near the Brooks School sign letting people know how fast they're going.

140
00:14:25,344 --> 00:14:28,927
To deter speeding would also help along with the traffic light.

141
00:14:28,947 --> 00:14:34,991
Hopefully we'll be able to deter any future accident that even could possibly happen at that location.

142
00:14:35,911 --> 00:14:40,854
We also need to take a look at, you know, all of our schools and make sure we have them all safe.

143
00:14:40,914 --> 00:14:46,678
And I know Walk Medford is doing a good job evaluating the community

144
00:14:47,423 --> 00:14:56,310
But I also believe there's a grant that was received, and I'm not sure if that went out for a proposal or how we're going to be spending that money, but I believe it hasn't been spent yet.

145
00:14:56,350 --> 00:15:12,742
And I think that's something we need to get on top of and make sure we make the appropriate changes at every location, everywhere in the community, because we just want to keep the pedestrians safe from, you know, and do everything we can to deter any accidents anywhere that could happen.

146
00:15:12,902 --> 00:15:14,643
So I just want to thank Councilor Carviello.

147
00:15:15,070 --> 00:15:30,082
second, the resolve and, um, move to amend it to as, as, as stated on the motion, uh, offered by, uh, council caviello, uh, seconded by vice president longer current and amended, uh, chair recognizes councilor Falco.

148
00:15:30,402 --> 00:15:31,323
Thank you, Mr. President.

149
00:15:31,343 --> 00:15:34,425
I'd also like to thank, uh, councilor Caviello for bringing this forward tonight.

150
00:15:35,026 --> 00:15:37,328
Um, this is an issue that, uh, needs to be addressed.

151
00:15:37,488 --> 00:15:44,093
It's long overdue and, uh, I would, uh, support the addition of a traffic light at that intersection, a hundred percent.

152
00:15:44,969 --> 00:15:48,231
The traffic is out of control down there.

153
00:15:48,972 --> 00:15:52,434
People seem to, no one pays attention to where they're driving.

154
00:15:52,454 --> 00:16:04,402
That goes everywhere, but I think in between when we get a traffic light put in and today, we need to come up with some steps to actually make this a safer intersection for our students.

155
00:16:04,996 --> 00:16:06,637
and for just everyone in general.

156
00:16:06,697 --> 00:16:15,561
And I think definitely additional signage, hopefully additional police presence, but I'd also like to see a crossing guard added in the morning for the middle school students.

157
00:16:16,062 --> 00:16:21,945
Right now we currently have one for the elementary school students, but I think that the middle school students also need one as well.

158
00:16:22,125 --> 00:16:30,449
I have received calls from parents that have kids in middle school and it is a very hard intersection to navigate in the morning.

159
00:16:30,983 --> 00:16:37,826
in the afternoon, and I believe that a crossing guard for the middle school students would be beneficial as well.

160
00:16:39,727 --> 00:16:46,610
I also talked to Superintendent Belson, and I was advocating for additional crossing guard with him as well.

161
00:16:47,131 --> 00:16:57,015
He had told me that, I guess there's going to be a meeting, I think on Thursday, between the mayor and the superintendent, and I think the police chief as well, and I think they're gonna hopefully work on a solution for this.

162
00:16:58,056 --> 00:17:00,757
But I also, and I also believe too that

163
00:17:02,183 --> 00:17:04,046
The city really needs to hire a traffic engineer.

164
00:17:04,066 --> 00:17:18,104
I think a traffic engineer would help with a lot of these problems just by looking at how our roads are set up, what we can do to keep our residents and everyone that passes through our city safe, and just make commuting in general safer.

165
00:17:18,745 --> 00:17:33,895
So I think that, you know, I'll keep advocating for that, but I think a traffic engineer is something that we desperately need in the city as more and more people move to our city and our city just becomes, I think, more popular as each day goes by with people wanting to move here, businesses wanting to set up here.

166
00:17:33,915 --> 00:17:36,736
So I think that's something that we desperately need.

167
00:17:38,217 --> 00:17:39,758
So I support this 100%.

168
00:17:40,199 --> 00:17:44,061
I thank Councilor Caviello for bringing this forward this morning, this morning, tonight.

169
00:17:44,646 --> 00:17:45,746
And it's been a long day.

170
00:17:46,166 --> 00:17:49,627
And I definitely support this resolution.

171
00:17:49,647 --> 00:17:49,947
So thank you.

172
00:17:50,047 --> 00:17:50,367
Thank you.

173
00:17:54,688 --> 00:17:58,709
So on today's motion, it's amended by Vice President Long and Kern and Councilor Falco.

174
00:17:59,089 --> 00:18:00,510
Chair recognizes Councilor Knight.

175
00:18:01,290 --> 00:18:02,570
Mr. President, thank you very much.

176
00:18:02,630 --> 00:18:10,872
And thank you to my colleagues for your input on this important issue.

177
00:18:10,892 --> 00:18:14,093
Having grown up in the area and attended the Brooks School and having been involved

178
00:18:14,988 --> 00:18:21,072
near accidents myself as a child in that intersection, I certainly understand the situation that's at hand, Mr. President.

179
00:18:22,453 --> 00:18:30,479
One of the things that I was thinking, listening to Councilor Caviello in his presentation would be, we do have a dock pickup area on Auburn Street.

180
00:18:30,599 --> 00:18:34,821
If this ordinance gets passed this evening, there's no guarantee that those lights are gonna be changed tomorrow.

181
00:18:35,262 --> 00:18:35,422
So.

182
00:18:51,136 --> 00:18:51,976
Do I sound like Sinatra?

183
00:18:54,518 --> 00:18:59,761
So, as I was saying, Mr. President, I think Councilor Caviello brings up some several good points, as does Councilor Falco.

184
00:19:00,642 --> 00:19:05,705
One thing that concerns me is that these events have been occurring quite frequently.

185
00:19:05,785 --> 00:19:10,048
They've been occurring for a number of years, and I believe there should be some reporting requirement that's taking place.

186
00:19:10,488 --> 00:19:11,209
at the school level.

187
00:19:11,909 --> 00:19:24,779
So I'm wondering if we can amend the resolution to request that the principal of the Brooks School, Suzanne Galluzzi, provide us with any suggestions or input that she may have in what she feels as though would make her job a little easier and make the students there safer.

188
00:19:24,819 --> 00:19:26,160
She's there every day, Mr. President.

189
00:19:26,200 --> 00:19:35,247
She also went to the Brooks School and grew up in the neighborhood, so I think she has a pretty good grasp and handle on the issues at hand, and I think that she'd be able to provide us with some very helpful information.

190
00:19:35,748 --> 00:19:49,436
And one of the other items I'd like her to look into, if possible, would be to move the pickup area to the rear end on Prescott Street, where there's a large lot that people can pull in and out of, where students can congregate free and absent of being right next to the main roadway, Mr. President.

191
00:19:49,456 --> 00:19:51,558
So those are the two items that I'd like to add to this matter.

192
00:19:51,898 --> 00:19:54,780
I appreciate the Councilor for bringing it forward and it's something that I support.

193
00:19:55,400 --> 00:19:55,740
Thank you.

194
00:19:55,820 --> 00:19:56,621
Thank you, Councilor.

195
00:19:57,121 --> 00:20:00,223
And as amended by Councilor Knight, Chair recognizes Councilor Marks.

196
00:20:01,823 --> 00:20:02,724
Thank you, Mr. President.

197
00:20:03,624 --> 00:20:05,245
I think there was a number of good suggestions.

198
00:20:05,365 --> 00:20:24,656
Often, um, there was a pilot program created, uh, I believe it was about three years ago at a request of this council, uh, to implement raised crosswalks throughout the community and other, uh, communities have been very successful, uh, in using raised crosswalks as a traffic calming approach.

199
00:20:25,396 --> 00:20:29,799
Um, and, uh, to date we've had one raised crosswalk,

200
00:20:30,532 --> 00:20:33,274
uh, which was implemented on Winthrop street.

201
00:20:33,935 --> 00:20:37,978
And we're still waiting for the other two as part of the pilot program.

202
00:20:38,839 --> 00:20:47,886
And I've asked the administration a dozen times and we have yet to get a response on, uh, when the other two race crosswalks will take place.

