further to go on that side is, um, I think if we can do that, that'd be greatly appreciated on my end that if we can ask to keep that closed for now until next week and then have a meeting with the disability commission in, uh, explaining in depth what this is with the, uh, department of transportation.

1439
02:03:08,053 --> 02:03:17,196
So the motion is to keep that bus stop closed until consultation with the DOT and disability commission is completed.

1440
02:03:17,596 --> 02:03:19,116
It's currently working now.

1441
02:03:19,357 --> 02:03:21,037
They're saying it will be reopened this evening.

1442
02:03:21,377 --> 02:03:24,758
That's what they told me tonight, this evening, this evening.

1443
02:03:24,798 --> 02:03:27,919
They're saying that everything will go back as, as it was in the past.

1444
02:03:27,979 --> 02:03:32,301
So, but there was also supposed to be done September 14th and that hasn't stopped.

1445
02:03:32,341 --> 02:03:36,742
So, and again, that leads to one of the questions we had that was, uh,

1446
02:03:38,037 --> 02:03:55,740
a big fear of mine was the safety of that stop during the construction, because I know in pretty demanding and loud voices, the DOT and the T has told us that it's not

1447
02:03:56,235 --> 02:04:02,478
the project's fault that the buses aren't pulling all the way up and getting close to the sidewalk, that there's plenty of space.

1448
02:04:03,078 --> 02:04:03,638
I've done that.

1449
02:04:03,878 --> 02:04:07,940
I traverse that route every single day just for that purpose.

1450
02:04:08,620 --> 02:04:17,084
And because of the extra barrels and the opening of that gate, there is absolutely no way the bus can go to that full length of what's needed under their law.

1451
02:04:17,464 --> 02:04:21,686
So, um, that opens up, I think, a big safety issue.

1452
02:04:21,726 --> 02:04:23,107
So I'm going to, um,

1453
02:04:24,035 --> 02:04:45,102
concur with my fellow colleague, and I hope the rest of our committee would agree, and then have a meeting as soon as possible with the Department of Transportation and the Disability Commission to look into this process of closing it until the end of that construction period on that side.

1454
02:04:45,122 --> 02:04:50,904
I'd like a motion for approval, Mr. President.

1455
02:04:55,785 --> 02:04:56,446
Thank you, Mr. President.

1456
02:04:56,466 --> 02:05:05,098
Mr. President, if we vote for approval tonight, if we could have the clerks send a letter to the TDC first thing in the morning, letting them know of our decision.

1457
02:05:06,360 --> 02:05:08,643
As amended by Councilor Caviello.

1458
02:05:09,264 --> 02:05:10,005
All those in favor.

1459
02:05:10,892 --> 02:05:11,572
All those opposed?

1460
02:05:11,873 --> 02:05:14,374
Motion carries.

1461
02:05:14,394 --> 02:05:15,955
16-659 offered by Councilor Falco.

1462
02:05:16,515 --> 02:05:37,825
Whereas the guardrail on Russell Street and Crane Street is in disrepair, whereas the guardrail is overgrown with weeds and brush and impedes walking on the sidewalk, be it resolved that in the interest of public safety, the guardrail be replaced and the weeds and brush be removed as soon as possible.

1463
02:05:38,246 --> 02:05:38,986
Councilor Falco.

1464
02:05:39,554 --> 02:05:40,355
Thank you, Mr. President.

1465
02:05:40,375 --> 02:05:41,295
A well-written motion.

1466
02:05:41,515 --> 02:05:42,196
Thank you very much.

1467
02:05:43,497 --> 02:05:44,458
Thank you, Mr. President.

1468
02:05:45,058 --> 02:05:53,344
I received a number of calls from the residents on Russell Street regarding the guardrail that it's basically on Russell Street.

1469
02:05:53,384 --> 02:05:55,786
And it stands between Russell Street and Crane Street.

1470
02:05:56,446 --> 02:05:59,528
And it's been in disrepair for quite some time now.

1471
02:05:59,949 --> 02:06:03,891
And it's also overgrown with lots of brush, and weeds, and trees, and whatnot.

1472
02:06:04,532 --> 02:06:07,754
And it's definitely a public safety concern.

1473
02:06:09,119 --> 02:06:11,020
I have a picture of it here if anybody wants to see it.

1474
02:06:11,300 --> 02:06:19,785
And it's really tough to, if anybody had any type of disability wanted to get by in a wheelchair, it'd be really tough to navigate.

1475
02:06:19,885 --> 02:06:20,886
It's really overgrown.

1476
02:06:21,346 --> 02:06:23,807
The guide rail is in complete disrepair.

1477
02:06:23,827 --> 02:06:24,828
It needs to be replaced.

1478
02:06:25,268 --> 02:06:27,890
And I'd like to see it replaced as soon as possible.

1479
02:06:28,470 --> 02:06:37,175
And if possible, at least if we could start by getting the DPW to trim the weeds and trim it back a bit just so people can,

1480
02:06:38,023 --> 02:06:39,144
traverse that sidewalk.

1481
02:06:39,624 --> 02:06:51,409
So I'd like to make a motion to have this approved and actually if we could have the guide rail replaced and if we could have the DPW in the meantime before its replacement, if we could have them clean up the area, I'd greatly appreciate it.

1482
02:06:52,049 --> 02:06:53,490
On that motion, all those in favor?

1483
02:06:53,710 --> 02:06:53,790
Aye.

1484
02:06:54,190 --> 02:06:54,871
All those opposed?

1485
02:06:54,931 --> 02:06:55,611
Motion carries.

1486
02:06:55,631 --> 02:06:56,351
16-660, whereas

1487
02:06:58,120 --> 02:07:16,174
offered by Councilor Falco, whereas all neighborhoods throughout our city are negatively impacted by graffiti and tagging, be it resolved that the city ordinance section 62 to 94 be updated to impose a fine to property owners for non-removal of graffiti or tagging.

1488
02:07:16,654 --> 02:07:17,395
Councilor Falco.

1489
02:07:18,536 --> 02:07:19,436
Thank you, Mr. President.

1490
02:07:20,217 --> 02:07:22,919
This here is an issue that

1491
02:07:23,487 --> 02:07:28,290
impacts or has a negative effect on all of our communities, all of our neighborhoods throughout the city.

1492
02:07:28,850 --> 02:07:35,654
As you drive around, you see graffiti, tagging on a lot of commercial property, it seems like.

1493
02:07:36,314 --> 02:07:51,063
And as I did some research, I found that there's penalties and fines for the person that actually tags the property, but there's no, we have nothing in the ordinance to actually

1494
02:07:51,604 --> 02:07:53,745
have the graffiti removed by the property owner.

1495
02:07:54,365 --> 02:08:05,409
And it's unfortunate, but I mean, Councilor Cabrillo had a great resolution earlier in the year where, you know, the Bigelow building on Forest Street, and that's a gateway to our square.

1496
02:08:05,989 --> 02:08:11,331
You come down Forest Street, you know, if you go to a show at the Chevalier or you're heading to Method Square, what do you see?

1497
02:08:11,371 --> 02:08:14,732
The building on the left and graffiti all over the side of the building.

1498
02:08:15,301 --> 02:08:20,325
It's been there for months and there's no teeth in the ordinance to actually have it cleaned.

1499
02:08:20,986 --> 02:08:26,870
So we can send out the code enforcement officer, but he really can't do anything about it because there's no teeth.

1500
02:08:26,890 --> 02:08:27,571
There's no fine.

1501
02:08:27,591 --> 02:08:28,071
There's nothing.

1502
02:08:28,852 --> 02:08:32,795
So, um, I really feel that, you know, something needs to be done about this.

1503
02:08:32,855 --> 02:08:39,260
I think, you know, maybe this paper goes into subcommittee where we research it and see what they do in other cities and towns, but something needs to be done.

1504
02:08:39,841 --> 02:08:43,804
Uh, you know, all over the city, I see graffiti and tagging and there's really,

1505
02:08:44,886 --> 02:08:46,106
There's nothing being done about it.

1506
02:08:46,466 --> 02:08:48,007
And I think something needs to be done.

1507
02:08:48,407 --> 02:08:53,128
It sends a message to people when they come to our community and they see this, they say, what's going on here?

1508
02:08:53,148 --> 02:08:54,788
I mean, there's graffiti everywhere.

1509
02:08:54,808 --> 02:08:56,248
And I think it really sends a message.

1510
02:08:57,008 --> 02:09:00,969
And the thing with graffiti and tagging, if you don't take it down right away, it gets worse.

1511
02:09:01,569 --> 02:09:05,170
And people add to it and it just multiplies and it gets out of control.

1512
02:09:05,230 --> 02:09:10,591
And I feel like we're at a point now where, you know, you go to each corner of the city, there are buildings that have it.

1513
02:09:11,015 --> 02:09:12,456
And something needs to be done about it.

1514
02:09:12,536 --> 02:09:17,638
So I'd like to offer this resolution, and I'd hope that everyone would support it.

1515
02:09:18,399 --> 02:09:30,325
And I think that going to subcommittee is probably the proper approach to take, because I think we should research it with other cities and towns to see what other cities and towns do, just to make sure that we're doing the right thing.

1516
02:09:31,086 --> 02:09:34,167
but I would like the council's support on this, so thank you.

1517
02:09:34,267 --> 02:09:34,607
Very good.

1518
02:09:34,647 --> 02:09:38,488
Zoning and ordinance would be the committee on that motion.

1519
02:09:38,548 --> 02:09:39,388
Councilor Caviello.

1520
02:09:39,508 --> 02:09:40,228
Thank you, Mr. President.

1521
02:09:40,528 --> 02:09:43,169
Mr. President, again, thank Councilor Falco.

1522
02:09:43,309 --> 02:09:47,730
Again, I brought up the big old building and the building right beside it multiple times.

1523
02:09:47,750 --> 02:09:49,290
The graffiti is still there.

1524
02:09:49,650 --> 02:09:56,171
And again, you know, we have meetings, but we want to build up the square, build a community.

1525
02:09:56,191 --> 02:09:58,772
This goes to the curb appeal of the city.

1526
02:09:59,223 --> 02:10:00,384
or curb appeal is horrible.

1527
02:10:00,984 --> 02:10:19,039
And again, you know, um, I, I don't know how to, uh, you know, put teeth into it, but you know, in the past, you know, the sheriff's department has come down and, uh, with the graffiti patrol and, uh, and, uh, and taking the graffiti down the past, maybe we can make it an appeal to a sheriff contusion, maybe come down again.

1528
02:10:19,099 --> 02:10:20,761
I don't know if they do private buildings.

1529
02:10:21,942 --> 02:10:24,604
Um, but again, uh, it's a, uh,

1530
02:10:25,245 --> 02:10:35,687
The curb appeal in our city is horrible, and as long as people go around tagging, and they're tagging all parts of the city, it just negatively impacts everybody.

1531
02:10:36,307 --> 02:10:42,548
So again, I support this motion, and I've had similar motions in the past, but I'd say the pain is still there.

1532
02:10:46,189 --> 02:10:47,549
Mr. President, thank you very much.

1533
02:10:47,569 --> 02:10:54,010
I certainly can appreciate the ordinance, and I think that back last session, Councilor Marks came up with actually

1534
02:10:55,049 --> 02:11:13,639
an excellent idea on a way to combat graffiti in private residences by creating a revolving graffiti removal account and having a graffiti removal team that will go out and speak with property owners who have been affected by graffiti and then, with their permission and waiver liability, be allowed to go onto the private property and remove that graffiti.

1535
02:11:14,040 --> 02:11:20,984
I think that this is a great opportunity for us to explore further what options and opportunities we have to address this problem.

1536
02:11:21,984 --> 02:11:23,265
I think that, you know, one of the things

1537
02:11:24,016 --> 02:11:26,798
that Councilor Marks put together was an actual team that will go out and do it.

1538
02:11:27,679 --> 02:11:41,028
And when we look at our DPW and some of the areas that we can improve on, I think that we might want to look at creating a permanent sign department that's responsible for the erecting of signs and the removal of graffiti in public and private places.

1539
02:11:41,088 --> 02:11:46,372
I think that this would be a great, great place to start for us to have the discussion and to jump off on speaking on it.

1540
02:11:46,592 --> 02:11:51,476
You know, Councilor Falco sits on the zoning and ordinance subcommittee with myself and Councilor Caviello.

1541
02:11:51,536 --> 02:11:52,697
And you know, I think that,

1542
02:11:53,875 --> 02:11:57,556
We have a work product that shows that we've been able to get things done when we met and worked together.

1543
02:11:57,616 --> 02:12:00,557
So, um, with that being said, I wholeheartedly support the ordinance.

1544
02:12:00,597 --> 02:12:04,218
I look forward to sitting down with my colleagues on the zoning subcommittee and addressing the issue.

1545
02:12:04,238 --> 02:12:04,678
Mr. President.

1546
02:12:07,999 --> 02:12:08,940
Thank you, Mr. President.

1547
02:12:09,140 --> 02:12:10,700
And yes, uh, console nights.

1548
02:12:10,760 --> 02:12:11,120
Correct.

1549
02:12:11,540 --> 02:12:20,063
I think it was about seven or eight months ago when console Caviello offered his resolution about, uh, finding owners that leave graffiti up.

1550
02:12:20,863 --> 02:12:23,484
And, uh, you know, I, I don't have a problem if,

1551
02:12:23,991 --> 02:12:34,617
The city approaches a business, and in this case, it could be a homeowner too, because we're saying business could be a homeowner, and after many attempts, the homeowner of the business says, you know what?

1552
02:12:35,077 --> 02:12:36,257
I'm not going to clean that off.

1553
02:12:36,618 --> 02:12:40,199
Then I think there should be teeth that you can go after the business or the homeowner.

1554
02:12:40,580 --> 02:12:46,883
The concern I have is I, as a homeowner, someone comes up Halloween night and spray paints the front of my house.

1555
02:12:48,257 --> 02:12:51,802
Whatever the ordinance reads, within 10 days, 14 days, I have to remove it.

1556
02:12:52,203 --> 02:12:53,605
That adds insult to injury.

1557
02:12:54,005 --> 02:12:57,010
So I just got my house spray painted.

1558
02:12:57,330 --> 02:13:00,956
It's probably going to cost me hundreds of dollars, if not $1,000 or $2,000 to remove it.

1559
02:13:03,419 --> 02:13:07,644
And then I have the city saying, if you don't remove it within X number of days, we're going to fine you.

1560
02:13:08,405 --> 02:13:11,688
I think it's, you know, it's a little too much.

1561
02:13:11,928 --> 02:13:13,410
I could see people that are leaving it up.

1562
02:13:13,810 --> 02:13:22,600
You know, the business that we refer to on Forest Street, that was cleaned off a number of times, and the tagging went back a number of times.

1563
02:13:23,164 --> 02:13:29,847
So it wasn't, you know, there may be some new stuff or some older stuff still up there, but I think we have to be very careful.

1564
02:13:30,187 --> 02:13:33,108
The City of Somerville has a great program.

1565
02:13:33,588 --> 02:13:38,010
First of all, on their website, they have a place where you can report graffiti.

1566
02:13:38,770 --> 02:13:42,771
Secondly, they have, what Councilor Knight was saying, they have an agreement.

1567
02:13:42,811 --> 02:13:46,333
It's called Removal of Graffiti Agreement and Release of Liability.

1568
02:13:47,225 --> 02:14:06,490
They will go to anyone's home, they will go to any business, if the business owner signs the liability form, and Councilor Scott Pelli can probably speak better than this than I can, and the liability form waives any type of liability that the city of Somerville may have in the process of cleaning this up.

1569
02:14:06,910 --> 02:14:10,630
But it's a great alternative to offer to people that were just wronged.

1570
02:14:11,031 --> 02:14:16,992
You know, most people, you know, don't ask to get their house graffitied or their garage graffitied or whatever it might be.

1571
02:14:17,432 --> 02:14:19,233
this is something that's done by vandals.

1572
02:14:19,953 --> 02:14:24,474
And I think to offer a service is a great suggestion.

1573
02:14:25,215 --> 02:14:29,976
And if you offer a service and someone doesn't want to take you up on it, then maybe we should have teeth.

1574
02:14:30,376 --> 02:14:32,237
We also have a clean it or lean it ordinance.

1575
02:14:32,777 --> 02:14:36,739
And the clean it or lean it ordinance, in my opinion, would apply to graffiti also.

1576
02:14:37,099 --> 02:14:38,540
And that calls for a penalty.

1577
02:14:38,620 --> 02:14:44,543
So I believe we can enforce the clean it or lean it on graffiti if need be.

1578
02:14:44,563 --> 02:14:49,345
You know, this city is very lax when it comes to any type of enforcement.

1579
02:14:50,266 --> 02:14:52,226
But I like what Somerville does.

1580
02:14:52,527 --> 02:14:53,807
I think this is a great idea.

1581
02:14:53,827 --> 02:14:57,189
I just don't want to penalize business owners or

1582
02:14:57,789 --> 02:15:05,811
residents that may have been tagged and saying, well, you better get that off or we're not going to only tag you, we're going to send you a bill on top of it.

1583
02:15:06,531 --> 02:15:07,852
So I have a problem with that.

1584
02:15:07,892 --> 02:15:15,134
But I think we can craft something that makes sense and possibly look at, like Councilor Knight mentioned, about having

1585
02:15:16,012 --> 02:15:22,093
you know, a dedicated office that will go out and do some graffiti removal in this community.

1586
02:15:23,093 --> 02:15:29,495
I had someone drop off today to my house because they saw this on the agenda, a bottle.

1587
02:15:30,455 --> 02:15:41,697
Actually, I'm glad they didn't put it in a briefcase or some other bag because it dropped off a bottle of, it's called clarinet.

1588
02:15:42,865 --> 02:15:46,108
And this is a substance that a lot of municipalities use.

1589
02:15:46,848 --> 02:15:48,330
You spray it on any new cement.

1590
02:15:48,730 --> 02:15:59,639
So when we did the Fast 14 project, you spray it on the cement that's holding up the bridges, and it makes it 100 times easier to remove graffiti.

1591
02:16:00,880 --> 02:16:04,984
And it's really, it's a cost-effective way of, at least the city doing it.

1592
02:16:05,004 --> 02:16:11,269
I wouldn't recommend people spraying their homes with this, but I think it's an effective way for municipalities

1593
02:16:11,732 --> 02:16:18,297
and in locations that are prone to, to, uh, graffiti, uh, to use this substance, uh, Mr. President.

1594
02:16:18,858 --> 02:16:24,823
And, uh, there's a lengthy, um, uh, material safety data sheet that came with it.

1595
02:16:25,403 --> 02:16:30,527
And if the city administration is interested, I'd be more than happy to pass this on.

1596
02:16:31,248 --> 02:16:38,254
Uh, I won't leave it at city hall because I don't want them thinking I'm leaving something around that, uh, could be construed as something else.

1597
02:16:38,934 --> 02:16:39,395
But, um,

1598
02:16:40,975 --> 02:16:44,596
I agree with this resolution, and I thank my council colleague for offering it.

1599
02:16:45,996 --> 02:16:46,717
Councilor Campbell.

1600
02:16:46,817 --> 02:16:47,377
Thank you, Mr. President.

1601
02:16:47,657 --> 02:16:54,479
Mr. President, I think it was Councilor Marks who offered the resolution for the city to go out and buy some equipment to do this.

1602
02:16:54,519 --> 02:16:59,160
I mean, it's only a pressure washer, a high-end pressure washer.

1603
02:16:59,560 --> 02:17:07,242
Again, not very expensive, and it's kind of a simple fix that could be done.

1604
02:17:09,349 --> 02:17:11,191
I mean, a lot of people have them in their homes.

1605
02:17:11,911 --> 02:17:15,013
But I say, I don't know why, I'm sure our city has one.

1606
02:17:16,014 --> 02:17:17,255
If we don't have one, we should have one.

1607
02:17:17,936 --> 02:17:25,381
And again, and if we did have one, but the people would sign the agreement.

1608
02:17:25,742 --> 02:17:27,523
The DPW could help these people out also.

1609
02:17:27,883 --> 02:17:31,966
But again, I support Councilor Falco's motion there.

1610
02:17:33,728 --> 02:17:34,388
Councilor Falco.

1611
02:17:34,609 --> 02:17:35,289
Thank you, Mr. President.

1612
02:17:37,024 --> 02:17:43,669
I thank my council colleagues for their suggestions because I think, you know, this at least starts the discussion as to what we can do.

1613
02:17:44,029 --> 02:17:51,795
I think some great suggestions came from Councilor Knight, Councilor Marks, Councilor Caviello with regard to actually maybe bringing on a team or having a department that does that.

1614
02:17:52,355 --> 02:17:56,838
And I think maybe incorporated with some teeth if someone refuses, you know, that's something we can look at.

1615
02:17:56,898 --> 02:17:59,540
But the discussion begins and I think that's the important piece.

1616
02:18:00,080 --> 02:18:02,582
And I just want to thank my colleagues for their support.

1617
02:18:02,802 --> 02:18:03,082
Thank you.

1618
02:18:03,122 --> 02:18:03,463
Thank you.

1619
02:18:03,483 --> 02:18:06,505
So on the motion for approval, citizen wishes to speak.

1620
02:18:08,999 --> 02:18:10,119
Hi, I'm Cheryl Rodriguez.

1621
02:18:10,159 --> 02:18:20,143
I live at 281 Park Street, and I saw this item on the agenda, and in the past couple of months, I've posted a couple of graffiti incidents that happened at the Roberts School.

1622
02:18:22,124 --> 02:18:27,026
So I posted for two months, someone had written on the side of the school, and the complaint wasn't acknowledged.

1623
02:18:27,546 --> 02:18:37,990
Finally, this past week, a private citizen messaged me and told me that they had gone down to the school with a bucket and water and a scrub brush and cleaned the graffiti off the school.

1624
02:18:39,500 --> 02:18:41,663
which thank you very much for cleaning the school.

1625
02:18:42,264 --> 02:18:44,747
I don't think he should have had to but I appreciate that he did that.

1626
02:18:45,148 --> 02:18:52,198
There's also a pedestrian crossing sign at the school that has had graffiti on it and the bottom rivet is not connected and that's been there for about two years.

1627
02:18:52,696 --> 02:18:55,199
I know several parents have called and complained about that.

1628
02:18:55,759 --> 02:19:01,285
So our DPW, I know, is short-staffed and they really are not able to handle this overflow.

1629
02:19:01,345 --> 02:19:04,408
So I think the graffiti issue in the city is probably more of a symptom.

1630
02:19:05,569 --> 02:19:08,132
I can also cite an example of businesses on Spring Street.

1631
02:19:08,653 --> 02:19:14,559
I drove down Spring Street and there was someone had written their name about 40 or 50 times on one building on Spring Street.

